Experimental implementation of Type Theory with Records

-- Cooper & Ginzburg, Handbook, 2015. Numbers refer to example numbers in the book chapter.
-- https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-01138034/file/rc-jg-ttrsem-final%20(1).pdf

Usage:

  runhaskell TryTTR          -- open TTR shell where expressions can be evaluated
                    <file>   -- type check file, open shell for evaluation in context of file
		    - nocheck <file>    -- the same, without type checking
		    - latex   <file>    -- convert file to latex code


Examples:

  runhaskell TryTTR ex2.ttr >ex2.tex   -- followed by pdflatex ex2.pdf
  runhaskell TryTTR ex3.ttr            -- for evaluation


To do:
- dependent type support
- subtyping

